(
<figureCitation box="[417,498,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,199,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Lophilema spp.: male genitalia. 15, L. mbulu, holotype, Tanzania, Mbulu Mts., slide AV3189; 16, L. bilobata, holotype, Kenya, Aberdare Range, slide AV4258; 17, L. claudei, holotype, Cameroon, slide ZSM Arct. 197/2017 Volynkin; 18, L. nguru, holotype, Tanzania, Nguru Mts., slide AV3311." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617747/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) by its distally narrower uncus, slightly shorter vinculum, narrower and more setose juxta, shorter dorsal crest of valva, situated more basally, narrower and less curved distal part of the dorsal section of the valva, significantly narrower sacculus, much longer and narrower distal saccular process, finer granulation and absence of a dorsal diverticulum of vesica. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin, 2019" authorityName="Volynkin" authorityYear="2019" box="[1053,1149,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lophilema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curva" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1053,1149,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">L. curva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1159,1251,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1159,1251,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1269,1353,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1850,1873]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1829]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 19–22. Lophilema spp.: male genitalia. 19, L. curva, holotype, Tanzania, Nguru Mts., slide AV3195; 20, L. fletcheri, holotype male, Uganda, Ruwenzori Range, slide NHMUK010314633 Volynkin (mounted in euparal from dried genital preparation by Kiriakoff) (©NHMUK); 21, L. creatoplaga, Kenya, slide NHMUK010314601 Volynkin (©NHMUK); 22, L. angustipennis, syntype of Ilema pilosa, Ghana, slide BMNH(E) Arct-233 (©NHMUK)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617749/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) by its distally narrower uncus, shorter and more smoothly curved dorsal crest of costa valvae, slightly broader dorsal section of the valva, more slender and straight distal saccular process, weaker granulation and absence of a dorsal diverticulum of the vesica; 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin, 2019" authorityName="Volynkin" authorityYear="2019" box="[456,552,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lophilema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nguru" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[456,552,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">L. nguru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[559,648,655,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[559,648,655,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiriakoff" authorityYear="1958" box="[796,918,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lophilema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fletcheri">
<emphasis box="[796,918,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">L. fletcheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[933,1015,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1850,1873]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,193,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1829]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 19–22. Lophilema spp.: male genitalia. 19, L. curva, holotype, Tanzania, Nguru Mts., slide AV3195; 20, L. fletcheri, holotype male, Uganda, Ruwenzori Range, slide NHMUK010314633 Volynkin (mounted in euparal from dried genital preparation by Kiriakoff) (©NHMUK); 21, L. creatoplaga, Kenya, slide NHMUK010314601 Volynkin (©NHMUK); 22, L. angustipennis, syntype of Ilema pilosa, Ghana, slide BMNH(E) Arct-233 (©NHMUK)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617749/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) by its distally much narrower uncus, longer juxta, broader dorsal section of the valva, somewhat broader sacculus, and longer and more slender distal saccular process; while differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1901" box="[556,719,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Ilema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creatoplaga">
<emphasis box="[556,719,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">L. creatoplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
